- Active students are those who are currently enrolled and participating in their programs;
- Programs that "involve computers" are those offered by departments with "Computer" in their name;
- Admission requirements mentioning "math" indicate that a mathematical background is necessary for enrollment.

- `student_id = 0` refers to a specific student in the database;
- `average_overall_mark` is the mean of all final marks a student has received across all courses;
- `average_attendance` is the mean of attendance percentages recorded for a student across all courses.

- "Shining star" refers to the top-performing faculty member based on student grades and the number of courses taught;
- "Consistently achieve the highest average grades" means having the highest average final marks across all courses taught;
- "Teach the most courses" is used to break ties when multiple faculty members have the same average grade.

- 'Shining stars' metaphorically refers to students who have excelled academically;
- 'Garden of Computer Science' metaphorically represents the program where these students are enrolled;
- 'Blossomed with an A' metaphorically indicates that the students have achieved a high grade in the course;
- 'Foundational course' refers to a course that is typically required and important for the program.

- "active students" refers to students who are currently active in the system;
- "outshining their usual growth" means the final mark in a specific course is higher than the student's average final mark across all completed courses;
- "spring (first semester)" refers to the first semester of the academic year.

- "shining stars" refers to active students;
- "academic constellation" refers to the programs in which students are enrolled;
- "set to graduate last" refers to the most recent graduation date in each program.

- The summer solstice in 2024 is on July 26;
- "Currently active" refers to students who have an `active_student` flag set to 1;
- "Across all departments" means the average is calculated for all departments combined.

- "blossoming scholars" refers to students;
- "fully bloomed" refers to having a final mark (i.e., `final_mark` is not null);
- "average marks" refers to the average of `final_mark` for each student.

- "Shining stars" refers to the top-performing students;
- "Academic garden" is a metaphor for the program in which students are enrolled;
- "Average final marks" are the calculated averages of the final marks for each student.

sql:
SELECT MAX(student_count) AS max_enrolled
FROM (
    SELECT program_id, COUNT(student_id) AS student_count
    FROM students
    GROUP BY program_id
);
